---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="KaijuFinance Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy Policy for KaijuFinance — a local-first personal finance app for Android by KaijuBytes."
>
  <section class="py-10">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2" style="color: var(--color-text);">KaijuFinance Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-sm mb-6" style="color: var(--color-muted);">
        <strong>Effective date:</strong> May 1, 2026 &nbsp;·&nbsp; <strong>Last updated:</strong> May 1, 2026
      </p>

      <div class="rounded-md p-4 mb-8 border-l-4" style="background: var(--color-surface); border-color: var(--color-accent);">
        <strong>Short version:</strong> KaijuFinance processes all of your financial data
        <em>entirely on your device</em>. KaijuBytes does not operate any servers, does not
        collect your financial information, and is not a Personal Information Controller (PIC)
        under Philippine Republic Act 10173 (Data Privacy Act of 2012).
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3" style="color: var(--color-text);">1. Who we are</h2>
      <p>
        KaijuFinance is developed and published by <strong>KaijuBytes</strong> (sole trader,
        Orlando G. Martinez / Lanz, Philippines). Contact:
        <a href="mailto:support@kaijubytes.dev" style="color: var(--color-accent);">support@kaijubytes.dev</a>.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3" style="color: var(--color-text);">2. What data KaijuFinance collects — and where it stays</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        All personal and financial data you enter or import into KaijuFinance is stored
        <em>exclusively on your device</em> in an encrypted local database (SQLite with
        SQLCipher AES-256 encryption, keyed by your passcode). KaijuBytes never transmits,
        stores, or has access to your financial data.
      </p>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse">
          <thead>
            <tr style="background: var(--color-surface);">
              <th class="border px-3 py-2 text-left font-semibold" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">Data type</th>
              <th class="border px-3 py-2 text-left font-semibold" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">Stored where</th>
              <th class="border px-3 py-2 text-left font-semibold" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">Sent to KaijuBytes?</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td class="border px-3 py-2" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">Transaction records, account balances, budgets, categories</td>
              <td class="border px-3 py-2" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">On-device SQLite (AES-256, passcode-keyed)</td>
              <td class="border px-3 py-2" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">No</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="background: var(--color-surface);">
              <td class="border px-3 py-2" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">Receipt photos taken via the camera or gallery</td>
              <td class="border px-3 py-2" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">On-device app-private storage</td>
              <td class="border px-3 py-2" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">No</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border px-3 py-2" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">OCR extraction results</td>
              <td class="border px-3 py-2" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">Processed entirely on-device (MLKit, on-device SLM)</td>
              <td class="border px-3 py-2" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">No</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="background: var(--color-surface);">
              <td class="border px-3 py-2" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">Bank and e-wallet notification text</td>
              <td class="border px-3 py-2" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">Processed on-device; transaction proposals stored locally</td>
              <td class="border px-3 py-2" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">No</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border px-3 py-2" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">Gmail message data (if email ingest is enabled)</td>
              <td class="border px-3 py-2" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">Read client-side; OAuth token stored in Android Keystore</td>
              <td class="border px-3 py-2" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">No — Google's servers serve the email; KaijuBytes never sees it</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="background: var(--color-surface);">
              <td class="border px-3 py-2" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">SALN declarations</td>
              <td class="border px-3 py-2" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">On-device database; PDF/DOCX exported to your device</td>
              <td class="border px-3 py-2" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">No</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border px-3 py-2" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">Passcode / biometric key material</td>
              <td class="border px-3 py-2" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">Android Keystore (hardware-backed on supported devices)</td>
              <td class="border px-3 py-2" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">No</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3" style="color: var(--color-text);">3. Permissions we request and why</h2>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse">
          <thead>
            <tr style="background: var(--color-surface);">
              <th class="border px-3 py-2 text-left font-semibold" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">Permission</th>
              <th class="border px-3 py-2 text-left font-semibold" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">Why</th>
              <th class="border px-3 py-2 text-left font-semibold" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">Can you deny it?</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td class="border px-3 py-2" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">Camera</td>
              <td class="border px-3 py-2" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">Scan receipts via the Smart Scan feature</td>
              <td class="border px-3 py-2" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">Yes — Smart Scan will not work; all other features unaffected</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="background: var(--color-surface);">
              <td class="border px-3 py-2" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">Read external storage / Media (Photos)</td>
              <td class="border px-3 py-2" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">Import receipt photos from your gallery</td>
              <td class="border px-3 py-2" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">Yes — gallery picker will not work; camera path unaffected</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border px-3 py-2" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">Notification Listener (BIND_NOTIFICATION_LISTENER_SERVICE)</td>
              <td class="border px-3 py-2" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">Detect bank and e-wallet transaction notifications from apps like BPI Mobile, BDO, GCash, Maya, and GoTyme — so you don't have to type every transaction manually. Notification text is parsed on-device and immediately discarded after a transaction proposal is created.</td>
              <td class="border px-3 py-2" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">Yes — automatic transaction detection will not work; manual entry unaffected. You can revoke at any time: Settings → Notification Access.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="background: var(--color-surface);">
              <td class="border px-3 py-2" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">Internet</td>
              <td class="border px-3 py-2" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">Required for: (a) downloading optional on-device AI models (Gemma 3n, Qwen2.5) on first use; (b) refreshing exchange rates (read-only public API, no PII sent); (c) Google AdMob (Free tier). No financial data is ever sent over the network.</td>
              <td class="border px-3 py-2" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">No — Android does not allow per-app Internet permission denial on modern versions</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border px-3 py-2" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">Google Sign-In (Gmail scope: gmail.readonly)</td>
              <td class="border px-3 py-2" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">Optional: parse bank confirmation emails for automatic transaction entry. Token stored in Android Keystore. KaijuBytes cannot read your Gmail — the token grants the app read-only access from your device only.</td>
              <td class="border px-3 py-2" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">Yes — you must explicitly connect your Gmail account; the feature is opt-in</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="background: var(--color-surface);">
              <td class="border px-3 py-2" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">USE_BIOMETRIC / USE_FINGERPRINT</td>
              <td class="border px-3 py-2" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">Optional biometric unlock in addition to passcode</td>
              <td class="border px-3 py-2" style="border-color: var(--color-border);">Yes — passcode login still works</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3" style="color: var(--color-text);">4. Google AdMob (Free tier only)</h2>
      <p class="mb-3">
        The Free tier of KaijuFinance displays advertisements served by <strong>Google AdMob</strong>.
        Google is the data controller for ad-targeting data collected through AdMob. KaijuBytes does
        not access this data. Google's privacy practices are governed by the
        <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--color-accent);">Google Privacy Policy</a>.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-3">
        If you are in the EU, EEA, or UK, a consent dialog (Google User Messaging Platform) will
        appear on first launch as required by GDPR and Google's policies. You can also toggle
        "Personalized Ads" off in <em>Settings → Privacy → Ad Preferences</em> at any time.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Pro subscribers</strong> see no advertisements; AdMob is inactive on Pro-tier sessions.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3" style="color: var(--color-text);">5. On-device AI models</h2>
      <p class="mb-3">Smart Scan uses local AI models to extract transaction details from receipts:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mb-3">
        <li><strong>MLKit Text Recognition</strong> — Google's on-device OCR API. Text is processed locally; see <a href="https://developers.google.com/ml-kit/terms" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--color-accent);">MLKit Terms</a>.</li>
        <li><strong>MiniLM (sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2)</strong> — Open-source model (Apache 2.0), runs entirely on-device.</li>
        <li><strong>Gemma 3n E2B / Qwen2.5-0.5B</strong> — Downloaded from HuggingFace or a KaijuBytes CDN when you first use Smart Scan on a supported device. These models run locally. No receipt text is sent to any server during inference.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Gemma 3n is governed by
        <a href="https://ai.google.dev/gemma/terms" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--color-accent);">Google's Gemma Terms of Use</a>;
        you must accept those terms before the model is downloaded. Qwen2.5 is Apache 2.0.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3" style="color: var(--color-text);">6. Data you export</h2>
      <p>
        When you use the backup or vault export features, KaijuFinance writes an encrypted file
        to your device (or a location you choose, such as OneDrive or a local folder). KaijuBytes
        does not receive this file. You are responsible for the security of any file you export
        to a cloud storage provider.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3" style="color: var(--color-text);">7. In-app purchases</h2>
      <p>
        Pro subscriptions are processed entirely by <strong>Google Play Billing</strong>.
        KaijuBytes receives only an anonymised purchase token from Google; we do not see your
        payment card details. See
        <a href="https://payments.google.com/payments/apis-secure/u/0/get_legal_document?ldo=0&ldt=privacynotice" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--color-accent);">Google Payments Privacy Notice</a>.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3" style="color: var(--color-text);">8. Children's privacy</h2>
      <p>
        KaijuFinance is not directed at children under 13 (or under 16 in the EU).
        We do not knowingly collect data from children.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3" style="color: var(--color-text);">9. Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        If we add server-side features in a future version (e.g. cloud sync, cloud Smart Scan),
        we will update this policy and notify you via an in-app banner before those features go
        live. The updated policy will be posted at this URL with a new effective date.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3" style="color: var(--color-text);">10. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions or concerns about this policy:<br />
        <a href="mailto:support@kaijubytes.dev" style="color: var(--color-accent);">support@kaijubytes.dev</a><br />
        KaijuBytes, Philippines
      </p>

      <footer class="mt-12 pt-6 text-sm" style="border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); color: var(--color-muted);">
        © 2026 Orlando G. Martinez (Lanz) / KaijuBytes. All rights reserved.
        KaijuFinance is not a regulated financial adviser. Information in the app
        is for personal budgeting and planning purposes only.
      </footer>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
